Being a developer in this team means you will be part of a young and growing team where your experience, skills and ideas are a key part of success. You will make a difference by improving the codebase, processes and of course the team itself.

WHERE YOU WILL LAND

A place with the atmosphere and freedom of a scale-up, combined with the professionality and resources of an established company.This organization enables travelers to enjoy Europe’s rail network in 31 countries. With a multicultural and passionate team, believing that creative thinking and diversity helps to improve the brand and ultimately create a unique experience for customers.

WORK TO BE DONE

· Develop new features for the Planner Android app;

· Work across disciplines with designers, content creators, product owner and test engineers;

· Active participation in planning and design decisions.

ABOUT YOU

You are an experienced developer with preferably a Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Computer Science or a related field with several years of experience with native Android development in Java. You have a solid understanding of object-oriented programming, design patterns, data structures, algorithms and mobile design principles. You’re up-to-date with the latest technologies related to Android development and features. You have experience with GIT (version control, github/gitlab/bitbucket/etc.) and with the Scrum Agile way of working. You’re able to work in cross functional teams and have strong communication skills. Understanding user feedback is one of your talents as well as interpreting user requirements. Experience or interest in Kotlin, Flutter, react native or with location-sensitive apps would be very cool.

WHY JOIN?

This is a growing organization that likes to help colleagues to grow as well. The work-life balance is awesome. It is a very positive and informal environment which helps to develop.

WE OFFER
• A very international and diverse environment where everyone is treated equally;
• Office within a 5 minute walking distance from Utrecht CS;
• An attractive salary and free train travels through The Netherlands and Europe;
• Full support to enjoy a good work-life balance;
• Relocation package; 2 night stay in our CONG HOME Hotel, Visa, Housing, financial & fiscal support;
• CONG Club Membership, being part of our global Tech, Digital, Data support network.

ABOUT CONG

Hi, we are CONG! We aren't just about bringing modern organizations together with the best developers, creators, makers and builders – CONG is a lifestyle! We facilitate, inspire and transform, while at the same time putting great importance on (job) satisfaction. That’s because people are more creative, more innovative and stronger when they’re feeling happy. We bring out the best in people, projects and organizations because the best results then follow. That’s why we are here, for you. That’s what makes us feel good!

Create your own future

As an intern, you will support the Digital Innovation & Analytics, Android team in the day-to-day development of our Android apps. You will work in a dynamic environment with a multidisciplinary native developers in our client tooling cluster for the Private Banking organisation.

You will use your talents as a Software Developer at Van Lanschot Kempen to inspire, support, and learn in your scrum team. You will work with other highly qualified people who are all focused on delivering value by developing our Android applications. Our values are: Personal, Specialised, Entrepreneurial and Decisive. Values you identify with.

You have the following tasks:
• Contribute to Product Backlog Items (PBIs) with your coding skills;
• Perform code reviews;
• Take part in the Quality Assurance process;
• Participate in all Scrum activities of the team you are part of, such as the daily stand-up, planning, retrospective, refinement, and sprint reviews.

Your talents

Creative, innovative, and digital savvy. This is how we can best describe you in the position of aspiring Software/Android Developer. Talents that you use to guide our users in a constantly changing world, every day. By thinking out-of-the-box and asking questions, you add value to the team you are part of.

In addition:
• You are a third- or fourth-year Bachelors or Master's student in software development (or similar);
• Analytical, result-oriented and have a hands-on mentality;
• You have development skills;
• You are open to learn Kotlin/Jetpack-Compose skills or have them already
• You are passionate about innovative technology and tools;
• You are people minded and eager to learn;
• You are available at least 32 per week for a minimum of 5 months;
• You have good mastery of English, both oral and written.

Move ahead at Van Lanschot Kempen

Investing in a more future-oriented, sustainable, and data-driven way with various clients. Both nationally and internationally. With almost 300 years of experience, we make this ambition a reality at Van Lanschot Kempen. We do this with some 2,000 colleagues in various fields of expertise.

The Digital Innovation & Analytics (DIA) department is a start-up-like environment within Van Lanschot Kempen. This means a work environment that offers both the energetic and ambitious character of a start-up and a large company's solid benefits. DIA was founded to help the organisation with its continuous digital and AI (Artificial Intelligence) transformation.

An organisation's degree of innovation and agility also depends on the diversity of its workforce. Our differences make us stronger together. We promote an inclusive work environment where all colleagues feel at home. With us, you can be yourself. And we are proud of that.

Curious about the stories of colleagues and how they experience working at Van Lanschot Kempen? Go to People & Projects and find out more!

Turning talent into value!

That’s what we do. The fact is, if you add value, you can obviously expect the same from us in return. A good work-life balance with our 'hybrid way of working' is a good example of this. In the Software Developer Internship, you will also be given:
• Compensation of € 850,00 gross per month (based on 40h per week);
• A company laptop;
• A cool start-up like environment where you cooperate with highly performing teams that build front-end applications for our clients and internal Private Banking colleagues;
• A lot of responsibility and a large amount of autonomy;
• An enthusiastic internship supervisor that is a senior in their field of expertise;
• The opportunity to work with the latest technologies (Angular, Azure, Github- and Microsoft Copilot and many more);
• Our custom CodeKickers program that offers a wide range of courses and workshops to allow you to hit the ground running and quickly update your technical knowledge;
• An environment to learn, make mistakes and develop yourself;
• The opportunity to have an impact in one of the largest Wealth Managers in The Netherlands.

Working on tomorrow's capital

Just the vacancy you were looking for? Please contact us.

Do you have any questions about the recruitment process? Please get in touch with Florencia Uhart, Campus Recruiter, f.uhart@vanlanschotkempen.com
